                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm being serious here. Is there anybody else that doesn't consider enchanters a dead class? Maybe I'm a sheep or something, but I honestly don't have a problem with OoW or the enchanter class in it. I find I still do CC (am I in the wrong zones?), I still get group invites, I can still solo for very acceptable xp (not in OoW zones mind you, but I don't know many classes that can solo in those higher level zones), and I still get to use a wide range of my abilities.
<br />

<br />
Am I wrong? And I'm not kidding here. *A lot* of people seem pissed off and are talking like they're pissed on and useless. I don't feel that way in the least on my enchanter, so I'm wondering if maybe I'm missing something completely obvious.
<br />

<br />
The charm nerf doesn't bother me, because I honestly don't think enchanters should be capable of that much dps in a pet, because I feel it trivializes some dps classes. I still mez a lot, I still find the chance to CC, I still get to do a lot, and I still feel I bring a lot to the groups I'm in.
<br />

<br />
Now I'm not being facetious when I ask - Am I wrong? Because I'm willing to accept that maybe I'm missing the big picture here, but to me, the big picture seems - well - not that bad to me.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />It's easy to use - if you're one of the 2% of the population who thinks logically and can read an instruction manual. The other 98% of the population would find it very hard or impossible to use.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
