                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Enchanters are still playable.
<br />

<br />
I think the problem is that we were once a fairly valued member of the group; groups now can pick a different class with similar skills making the group much more efficient.  We were part of that holy triumvirate (cleric, tank, enc), but there were a lot of complaints that every group had to have all three classes in order to do content.  Since Kunark, we've seen quite a decline in the utility of our class, and this is simply the last straw for a number of people.
<br />

<br />
The upgrade to spell lines and class abilities that are less and less used increases the feeling of being left behind and undesirable.  While we still have our core abilities, playing an enchanter now is much less about control and much more about buffing and slowing.  This is why people are upset.  The game is no longer challenging and engaging.  You can bot an ENC pretty easily because for the most part, CC is done by pulling, other classes have slows, and about the only thing you really need to pay attention to is when the buffs fade.
<br />

<br />
When it comes to the point where the majority of your concentration is on what programming is on the T.V. rather than what pulls are coming in, there's a problem.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=406237" target="_blank" class="postlink">Baalazai</a>
<br />
Rodcet Nife
<br />
<a href="http://www.echoesineternity.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Echoes in Eternity</a>
<br />

<br />
