                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm comparing CC to when CC was most fun.  Ie, Kunark/Original.
<br />

<br />
I'm comparing Charming to when Charming was most fun.  Ie, PoP/GoD.
<br />

<br />
I'm comparing having an enchanter bot with a bard in the group to having a bard bot with an enchanter in the group, and I can't find a situation where you'd rather have the person playing the enchanter mainly, short of at best some scripted raids.
<br />

<br />
I'm watching SOE change how charm works from under the enchanter, with no warning and no communication beyond some hearsay to a privledged few.  Look at how they handled the bard pbaoe nerf: pointed out the problem, solicited solutions, and found one that as narrowly as they could that fixed the problem.  Or even rangers, who got told that archery was dead.  Instead we get "this is not a nerf" and "it is just another add".
<br />

<br />
Right now, it makes more sense for an enchanter to chain nuke and use an animation than charm a mob.  It makes more sense to do out of camp crowd control and get enchanter buffs in PoK.  Not everyone out there has realized it yet.  Maybe the enchatners explaining it to them will make them realize it faster, but it sure seems true to me.  I've seen how useful we are in zones like KT where mobs are single pulled and there is no charm.  And I haven't seen an OoW zone where single pulling isn't far preferable to mezzing.
<br />

<br />
And that is why I'm upset.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
