                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Thanks for the replies. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> I think I've figured it why I seem to be thinking differently from a vast majority of people here ...
<br />

<br />
I'm not thinking from an enchanters point of view.
<br />

<br />
This doesn't make me right, nor does it make me wrong. It just means I'm seeing things from a different perspective then a lot of people.
<br />

<br />
I don't think enchanters should be required for groups, nor do I think there should be 5 adds per pull. I *do* think that a majority of the time, you should be able to get a single pull.
<br />

<br />
I don't think charmed pets should do more dps then a melee class. (by the same token, given the charm changes, I *do* think there should be a resist mod to make OoW charms easier to land, such that an enchanter with TD3 casting charm should get a full duration charm without tash 60% of the time)
<br />

<br />
So I really do understand why people are pissed off - for a lot of people, this is *their* class, and I can see that a lot of the abilities of the enchanter class have been eroded.
<br />

<br />
It's just that I see this as something that is - if not good - then not completely bad. Class balance is a very delicate thing, but I think classes are more in balance now then every before.
<br />

<br />
But that's just my perspective, and as (if) I move deeper into OoW, my perspective might change.
<br />

<br />
I just hope that people keep an open mind when they look at what's happened to the enchanter class, and instead of comparing it to how we *used* to be, compare it to how we *should* be in the context of the game and balance.
<br />

<br />
I'm probably wrong, but I still don't think we're bad off.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />It's easy to use - if you're one of the 2% of the population who thinks logically and can read an instruction manual. The other 98% of the population would find it very hard or impossible to use.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
