                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">At one time you used to hear in guild chat people asking for a CC class, be it bard or enchanter it did not matter to much.  I do not remember the last time a group asked for a CC class, but I do hear all the time a group looking for a slowing class.  
<br />

<br />
As a slowing class we have a hard time competing against other slowing classes that not only can tank a lot better then us, but also slow faster then us.  And to top it off, tash and slow generates a lot more aggro then what the other slowing classes use.
<br />

<br />
Not to many enchanters pick our class for its slowing abilities, if we loved slowing that much we would have created a shaman.  Most of us pick our class for its CC abilities and to a lesser degree for many people charming.  Buffing, slowing and nuking were just added bonus to picking our class, not the central reason to playing it. 
<br />

<br />
It is not often you see more then two mobs inc in OOW, and it has become safer for a group to have a shaman or a BL to just off tank the slowed mobs then to have a enchanter die trying to mez it.
<br />

<br />
A long time ago we were very desirable because groups needed CC and because we were the best drug dealers in the game with our mana regen buffs and our haste buffs.  These days it is easy for a group to purchase a 4 hour KEI.  We lost our edge, other classes have caught up to our mana regen and hasting abilities, while we were not given anything in return.
<br />

<br />
Between malos and balance of nihil, shamans have a minus 90 resistadj, with a lot less aggro then we do with tash and forlorn which is only a minus 50 resistadj.
<br />

<br />
I used to pull a lot in the old days, it would be nice if they gave us tools to help us pull if they are not willing to let us charm or CC anymore.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
