                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Enchanters are still playable but a shadow of what they once were.  You seem satisfied with the lower expectations of what enchanters should be able to do.  That is a perfectably acceptable point of view, one I think most of us are eventually going to have to take, given the anti-charm attitude SOE has taken in EQ, at least if we want to continue playing enchanters.
<br />

<br />
You echo the same sentiment shared by those who do not understand the nature of the charm nerf.  You accept the reduced DPS; that however is not the issue.  You ignore the dangers of maintaining a pet with that reduced DPS.  The benefit of charming a pet was reduced -- and perhaps rightfully so for the reasons you stated.  However, the risk for charming pets in Omens stayed the same -- unacceptably high, given the reduced benefit of charming.
<br />

<br />
There is also an additional problem aside from the modified damage tables in Omens zones; non-Omens monsters level 65 and up are flagged uncharmable, even if they fall within the level range of Compel and True Name.  Rather than do the additional work of giving every 65+ monster a modified damage table, they just flagged everything uncharmable.  That is, in my opinion, even worse than what they did to Omens.
<br />

<br />
It sounds like you're the kind of enchanter who never did much charming anyways so you and many others who are that way weren't as bothered by the changes.  Imagine if you were a mage and couldn't summon your Omens pets in non-Omens zones; it wouldn't bother you if you never bothered to get your Omens pet spells, now would it?</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=824212" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Provender</a>, High Elf Coercer (retired)
