                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>QenyaStarfury wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Thanks for the replies. :) I think I've figured it why I seem to be thinking differently from a vast majority of people here ...
<br />

<br />
I'm not thinking from an enchanters point of view.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Let me guess, you multi box and play many classes?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">This doesn't make me right, nor does it make me wrong. It just means I'm seeing things from a different perspective then a lot of people.
<br />

<br />
I don't think enchanters should be required for groups, nor do I think there should be 5 adds per pull. I *do* think that a majority of the time, you should be able to get a single pull.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The core, essence of the enchanter class, what made the enchanter fun way back when, was controlling crowds.
<br />

<br />
Can you balance the enchanter as a weak mage-varient with slow and buffs and mez as an emergency tool?  Yes.  But this is not a class I want to play.  This isn't the enchanter class.  It is some class they call "enchanter" and is distantly related to it.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I just hope that people keep an open mind when they look at what's happened to the enchanter class, and instead of comparing it to how we *used* to be, compare it to how we *should* be in the context of the game and balance.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
We should be a class that is fun to play.
<br />

<br />
I mean, balance wise, you could take the enchanter class, delete it, and replace it with a copy of the wizard class.  The game would be balanced.
<br />

<br />
I don't want to play a wizard.
<br />
I don't want to play a shaman.
<br />
I don't want to play a mage.
<br />
I don't want to play a beastlord.
<br />

<br />
You can balance classes all you want, but if along the way you kill a class don't expect those who love the class to thank you for it.
<br />

<br />
Changing enchanter gameplay so they play more like wizards, shamans, mages or beastlords is not acceptable to me.
<br />

<br />
They are all interesting classes, none of them are for me.
<br />

<br />
When incamp crowd control died, I adapted and learned to charm.
<br />

<br />
Now charm is dead.  Mez is dead.  It makes more sense to nuke and /pet attack with an animation while half afk watching TV than it does to charm a mob.
<br />

<br />
People who play enchanters as buffbots, or one head in a hydra, or emergency backup crowd control for their puller, they will see the changes to the enchanter class differently.  To them, every reduction in attention the enchanter class requires is a <span style="font-weight: bold">good</span> thing.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
