                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">QenyaStarfury,
<br />

<br />
The statement that Brenlo made about the future of the game is what concerns me the most: "we will continue to scale up npcs faster than we will scale up players".
<br />

<br />
That has a huge implication for our class and accounts for why most of our skills are being taken away from us.
<br />

<br />
1. Charm.  If the mobs are scale up faster than players, then it means our charmed mob is going to do more and more dps compare to a player.  In Vxed and Tipt, our charmed pet was doing about 3 rogues worth (according to Brenlo).  This descrepency is going to increase in the future...that is how they are making the game.  Therefor, you cant allow charm anymore....that's why its dead and will remain that way.
<br />

<br />
2.  Mez and CC.  I remember the prekunark and kunark days when the cleric actually had a chance to heal you on mez fails.  Today with the mobs scaling up faster than we do...they are killing us in one round...faster than any cleric can heal....it is only going to get worse.  Who in their right mind is going to mez in the future...you are basically guarantee a death in the near future....it is now more reliable to tank mez...tank/healer....at least they can still take the damage and be healed.
<br />

<br />
3. DPS.  Umm...we didnt get any significant upgrades here.  We probably nuke like a wizzy 10 to 15 levels below us.  In a pickup group (not with your friends), who is going to ask you based on your dps.
<br />

<br />
4.  Buffs.  There is probably only 3 buffs I cast; clarity, haste and magic resist....and you dont have to be in the group for them to get those....heck alot of players have a chanter buffbott sitting outside of their group giving them this.
<br />

<br />
5. Debuffs.  We dont have the best magic debuffer.  We dont have the best slow (plus it takes a long time to cast it).  Others can cripple and dispell magic.
<br />

<br />
6. Fear.  Well thats been gone for a long time.  Guess they didnt want reverse kiting after mobs 55+.
<br />

<br />
7. Stuns.  I use to have 2 stuns up to control unintentional large pulls.  They didnt like AE groups and so these have been gone for a while.  In Vxed and Tipt, wizzies, druids, pallys and cleric could stun where we couldnt.
<br />

<br />
If you were in a pickup group, why would you want an enchanter?  Pre Kunark, we were like experience modifiers (have an enchanter in your group and your group got exp alot faster)....today we are exp leeches, hehe (we dont add dps, our buffs can be gotten without us in the group).
<br />

<br />
I personally think, that SOE had to make a choice between the enchanter and bard class.  They basically gave the bard class all the mind altering "buffs"....i.e....they have better mana regen song than we do with even our c6.....they have crit modifiers so nukers can get up to 30% more damage (they may have gotten an upgrade with OoW)...their resist song blows us out of the water....they can fade (my god, what would the enchanter class would have been with an FD like ability)....they can pacify....they can mez....they can charm...they can even slow/haste/modify attack.  Basically they are letting the enchanter class die.  It was probably too hard to write encounters with and without us (given our ability to lock down some pretty mean mobs).  We either were too overpowering or spectators (when things are all tagged non mezz, non charm, non stun).  The nice thing with bards is that they have to be in your group to get those nice buffs....you dont need that with the enchanter class with so many pimping our buffs in pok.
<br />

<br />
Skil</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
