                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">By the way, I hope I'm not coming across as an soe fanboi here. In my opinion, the thing most wrong with the enchanter class (with *all* classes) is the abhorant lack of communication from Brenlo. It's just pathetic and sad that we have to hear about nerfs from a player, just as it's friggin' stupid how Brenlo speaks to the class base. I still can't get over the bard nerf, when he basically said "We're nerfing swarm kiting. Sorry, all you cheaters can't cheat the system any more ... CHEATERS!"
<br />

<br />
*This* is communication??? Now you want me to support a cause, I'll support any action to get SoE to talk with us instead of talking at us in such an insulting manner.
<br />

<br />
But as for enchanters - I do probably play differently then most people. I solo charm 50% of the time I play (alternating between HoH and PoT, with a sprinkle of 'fun' charming sessions, like Chardok / Vxed / Riwwi thrown in), and in groups I always used to charm. In OoW, I've pretty much given up charming, because people are right - why deal with a charmed pet that does such low dps and causes such a danger every 5 seconds to 7 minutes?
<br />

<br />
And that's where one of the biggest problems comes into play - the way charm is now, it's really most effective soloing. Tash, even with TD3, is pretty much required to have charm stick. So you'll never use charm as straight CC, because first you'll mez or root, then tash, *then* charm. This is about 20 seconds to deal with a single add - and what's the point? You get a 4 pull you're not going to take 20 seconds to get 1 under control.
<br />

<br />
I'd love to see charm get a negative 60 resist modifier that *ignores* tash. That way charms are inherently -60, but you can't bring them down to -120 by tashing first. I think that would solo a lot of problems.
<br />

<br />
But if charm was kept 'unnerfed', then enchanters would be the only class soloing in OoW, because in the right hands, it can be truly overpowered. And I know people are going to say "Don't ruin an ability because a few people are good at it" ... but I think more then a few are good at it. I mean, really - tash mob, run and root, charm, haste, dual wield - get another mob, pet attack - BAM ... dead in 10 seconds. It's honestly not that hard. And this would simply not be right in a new expansion.
<br />

<br />
So yeah, I agree with the nerf to charm in OoW zones. I don't agree with the implementation, however, but I think it's better then leaving it as it was before.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />It's easy to use - if you're one of the 2% of the population who thinks logically and can read an instruction manual. The other 98% of the population would find it very hard or impossible to use.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
