And that's what I think is wrong. I LOVE Sebilis - oh my god, the rush I used to get down there!!! 10 frogs inc! Train derailed! I have a LOT of great memories of playing down there. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
But is it really fair that a single class be needed for an "exp group?" That's what I'm talking about by the big picture. If you *require* an enchanter to be successful, then class balance is dead.
<br />

<br />
I also think people forgot that it's not always easy to single pull. I fought in the WoS the other night, and literally every 2nd pull had an add, the aggro range was so huge. If the monk had to stop and feign pull every single time to get down to one, then the pace of the action would be much slower. As it was, he'd go out and pull 2 or 3, and we were almost never without a mob in camp. Without an enchanter there, the pace would have slowed by more then a bit.
<br />

<br />
So yeah, I still feel useful as an enchanter (again, maybe I'm just playing in the wrong zones or with bad pullers) - not Sebilis useful, but I feel like I'm playing my part none the less.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />It's easy to use - if you're one of the 2% of the population who thinks logically and can read an instruction manual. The other 98% of the population would find it very hard or impossible to use.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
