<br />
Actually, your group's pace would have been the same with a shaman and faster with a bard/beastlord than with you.  WoS mobs put out crappy dps and have low MR.  Beastlords and shaman could have slowed the add easily and tanked the add for the duration of the fight.  Beastlords also can add considerable amounts of damage and Paragon for mana regen that rivals our own.  The bard wouldn't have any sort of agro from mezzing that mob while it was in camp so any tank could have just broken mez and start tanking whereas an enchanter probably required the tank to stun/snare/taunt before breaking and still end up having agro some of the time.  Anything that takes away from efficient killing slows you down.
<br />

<br />
Enchanters aren't useless in WoS as I play one quite effectively there, but you're deluding yourself if you think your WoS group couldn't have performed just as well or better without one.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Judge me by what I write, and not what I <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104900" target="_blank" class="postlink">wear</a>.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
